Cake recipe: Great - I don't know why some people said they turned out like muffins. I was careful while measuring and mixing (didn't pack the flour; didn't overmix) and I also made sure to take them out of the oven right before they seemed done. I think this sometimes makes the difference between moist and dry baked goods. Reducing the coconut milk was messy and took a while. Oh, well. At least it tastes like real coconut and not fake coconut flavor. I would definitely make the cupcakes again. Frosting recipe: This could use some tweaking according to a person's taste. I found the frosting to be too soft. I think there should be less butter and more sugar so the frosting would be stiffer and more stable. It's June here and this frosting does not like to get warm. It tasted great; I would just be ready to adjust the proportions somewhat.

