Rating: 4
These were excellent. Made a half batch as a test before making these for a big party, and cut the sugar in the batter to 1 cup as per other reviews here. Will maintain the cut-back when making full batches, as there is no need for them to be any sweeter. Extra vanilla in both batter and frosting is a nice touch. Also added a squeeze of lemon to the frosting, which always helps to lift it beyond just "sweet." The reduced coconut is fantastic: resist the urge to bump it up with coconut extract, as these have a nice, light taste of clean, fresh coconut as is. Extract would probably add an artificial dimension. That natural coconut taste is what sets these apart from most coconut baked goods and why guests will remember them. Oh, and one more thing: under-bake them slightly. If you let them get to the point where a wooden tester comes out clean, they will not be as moist as they could be. Rather, bake only until the very center is still wet - the result will be insanely moist. The tops of these did not come out as smooth domes, but a bit bumpy and craggy; no matter though, as the frosting hides the tops.

