Rating: 4
Thanks to all the previous reviewers! Because of your tips, these cupcakes came out perfectly. They were definitely cake-like, not muffin-like. Here are the changes I made: - Let the coconut milk reduce for over an hour, and added 1 tsp. coconut extract while it cooled. - Used cake flour; note you have to add an extra 2 tbsps for each cup when subbing cake flour for AP. - Sifted the cake flour, baking powder, and salt together. - Added vanilla bean seeds from 1 pod and 1 tsp of vanilla extract to the batter & also to the frosting. These cupcakes were an enormous hit, there wasn't a single one left. It's possibly the best thing I've ever baked.

